## Appendix

### Helper functions `ifelse()` and `case_when()`

`ifelse()` is a great help for all recoding tasks: we formulate a condition and if it is met, the first value is used; if not, the second value is used. Here we check whether `studs-mean(studs)` is greater than `0` - if so, `above` is used, otherwise `below`:




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
dat3 %>% mutate(rel_to_mean = studs-mean(studs),
                ab_mean_lab = ifelse(rel_to_mean > 0,"above","below"))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
  studs profs gegr prom_recht                uni rel_to_mean ab_mean_lab
1 19173   322 1971       TRUE         Uni Bremen   -2517.625       below
2  5333    67 1830       TRUE         Uni Vechta  -16357.625       below
3 15643   210 1973       TRUE      Uni Oldenburg   -6047.625       below
4 14954   250 1971      FALSE          FH Aachen   -6736.625       below
5 47269   553 1870       TRUE        RWTH Aachen   25578.375       above
6 23659   438 1457       TRUE       Uni Freiburg    1968.375       above
7  9415   150 1818       TRUE           Uni Bonn  -12275.625       below
8 38079   636 1995      FALSE FH Bonn-Rhein-Sieg   16388.375       above
```


:::
:::




`case_when()` (`{dplyr}`) extends this principle, allowing us to specify more than two options.  
The syntax is slightly different: first, we specify the condition, then after a `~` the values to be used: 




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
dat3 %>% mutate(age = case_when(gegr < 1500 ~ "very old",
                                gegr < 1900 ~ "old"))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
  studs profs gegr prom_recht                uni      age
1 19173   322 1971       TRUE         Uni Bremen     <NA>
2  5333    67 1830       TRUE         Uni Vechta      old
3 15643   210 1973       TRUE      Uni Oldenburg     <NA>
4 14954   250 1971      FALSE          FH Aachen     <NA>
5 47269   553 1870       TRUE        RWTH Aachen      old
6 23659   438 1457       TRUE       Uni Freiburg very old
7  9415   150 1818       TRUE           Uni Bonn      old
8 38079   636 1995      FALSE FH Bonn-Rhein-Sieg     <NA>
```


:::
:::




With `TRUE`, we can address all cases that have not met any conditions so far:



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
dat3 %>% mutate(age = case_when(gegr < 1500 ~ "very old",
                                gegr < 1900 ~ "old",
                                TRUE ~ "relatively new"))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
  studs profs gegr prom_recht                uni            age
1 19173   322 1971       TRUE         Uni Bremen relatively new
2  5333    67 1830       TRUE         Uni Vechta            old
3 15643   210 1973       TRUE      Uni Oldenburg relatively new
4 14954   250 1971      FALSE          FH Aachen relatively new
5 47269   553 1870       TRUE        RWTH Aachen            old
6 23659   438 1457       TRUE       Uni Freiburg       very old
7  9415   150 1818       TRUE           Uni Bonn            old
8 38079   636 1995      FALSE FH Bonn-Rhein-Sieg relatively new
```


:::
:::




This doesn't have to be limited to one variable:




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
dat3 %>% mutate(age = case_when(gegr < 1500 & prom_recht  == T ~ "very old university",
                                gegr < 1900 & prom_recht  == T ~ "old university",
                                gegr > 1900 & prom_recht  == T ~ "young university",
                                gegr < 1900 & prom_recht  == F ~ "old college",
                                gegr > 1900 & prom_recht  == F ~ "young college"))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
  studs profs gegr prom_recht                uni                 age
1 19173   322 1971       TRUE         Uni Bremen    young university
2  5333    67 1830       TRUE         Uni Vechta      old university
3 15643   210 1973       TRUE      Uni Oldenburg    young university
4 14954   250 1971      FALSE          FH Aachen       young college
5 47269   553 1870       TRUE        RWTH Aachen      old university
6 23659   438 1457       TRUE       Uni Freiburg very old university
7  9415   150 1818       TRUE           Uni Bonn      old university
8 38079   636 1995      FALSE FH Bonn-Rhein-Sieg       young college
```


:::
:::




